channel.title: Cleaned czar v5 20k lines removed packaged woooooop
channel.description:
This is the last version that will be released. It is now about clean enough that I can build on it without needing to lie down every few minutes. Feel free to continue cleaning and releasing yourself though.
Updates in this version Packaged More stuff removed It was mainly that I packaged it ALL BY MYSELF TAKE THAT TELENIM So yeah not many changes. But the packaged thing was a big thing for me never done it before.
Updates from V4 Event manager. More info file is now about 5 lines. More crap removed. Added a wearing handler. Moved all the timers out of process they are now handled by the event manager Conventions are now included in most of the files. (Takes ages)
Updates from V3 The client .java is now only 24k lines I have spent a lot of the saving methods in this version: No longer saves in .dats Handler for the saving methods. Moved some ints from client.java to player.java Deleted quite a lot of unnessary stuff You would not believe the amount of trash I found. Removed some useless handlers e.g Savegamehandler and another one playersave or something.
Updates from V2 Cleaned further. Command Handler. Action button handler. Fully working ip ban(Done properly) Completely configured to work with Stewie's client No long runs like a Czar I prefer to think of it as running like a Tate. Seperated Java and Class files.
Server download:) http://uppit.com/v/Z2WEYWJG
It is configured for Stewie's client from R00n-S3rv3r.
if you edit though will work for any client.
